{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: the failure boundary is module handoff (three collectors -> aggregation payload -> summary step), not a single pure function. REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: real network is not required to catch this specific failure; in-process source fakes plus a spy on the summary input can expose missing/overwritten sections. LLM-DEP: rejected Agentic because behavior text is about \"content passed\" to generation, not whether model output is good. REJECTION-GATE: System rejected because behavior does not require real OS/network/subprocess; Agentic rejected because no assertion on model decision/output quality.","test_description":"Wire real collection/orchestration modules with stub adapters for metrics, issue tracker, and deployment log. Execute one run and assert the exact payload handed to summary generation contains all three source sections with correct field mapping and no dropped source.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this is cross-module error propagation (source adapter failure -> report composer fallback text -> continued pipeline). A single-function unit test is too narrow. REAL-INFRA: unavailable source can be represented by adapter error/timeout exception without real network. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no mandatory real OS/network to reproduce this behavior wording; (b) no model-output correctness requirement; (c) no multi-agentic chain. REJECTION-GATE: System rejected because behavior text says only \"one data source is unavailable\" and does not require validating real transport-layer behavior.","test_description":"Run orchestration with two healthy source fakes and one failing source fake (e.g., raises timeout). Assert run completes, report includes explicit `data unavailable` marker for only the failed section, and other sections still contain data.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness depends on generated narrative fidelity to input values (representation accuracy), which is model-output quality, not just wrapper logic. A deterministic stub would always pass and hide hallucination/omission failures. MULTI-STEP: single generation judgment, so not Workflow. REJECTION-GATE: Integration rejected because behavior text explicitly requires \"accurately represents\" narrative content, which depends on real model decisions.","test_description":"Use a fixed hard-case canary set of input reports with known key values and edge cases (close numbers, mixed trends, missing section). Call the real summary model and score outputs against required factual checks (value presence/correctness, no contradictions) with pass thresholds over repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: this boundary is end-to-end delivery into a real inbox (network/email service behavior). In-process mocks can hide SMTP/API auth, envelope formatting, and provider acceptance issues. LLM-DEP: higher Agentic level considered but rejected because behavior text is delivery outcome (\"reaches ... inbox correctly\"), not summary quality. MULTI-STEP agentic chain is not required by the assertion. REJECTION-GATE: Agentic rejected by explicit focus on inbox delivery; Workflow rejected because no requirement to validate multiple model decisions.","test_description":"Run the script in an environment with reachable test instances of the three data sources and a real test email account/service. Verify one scheduled run produces and sends the report, and the message arrives in the configured inbox with expected subject/body sections and recipient addressing.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: behavior explicitly spans unreachable email transport plus durable local-file fallback plus next-run retry, which is sensitive to real filesystem/process-run boundaries. MOCK-HIDE: mocked mail/fs can miss real write/flush/path/permission and reconnection behaviors. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no required model-quality assertion, so not Agentic; no multi-agentic sequence, so not Workflow. REJECTION-GATE: Integration rejected because wording requires persistence and retry across scheduled runs, a real infra boundary.","test_description":"Execute run 1 with email endpoint intentionally unreachable; assert report file is persisted on disk in configured fallback path. Execute run 2 (next schedule) with email restored; assert queued fallback report is retried/sent and fallback state is cleared or marked delivered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.04}}]}
